Gate the raid1/raid10 `lim.features |= BLK_FEAT_ATOMIC_WRITES` assignment on the
pre-6.11 queue_limits.features field — composed meshstor-main variant.

Companion to 0005 (which gates the md.c md_init_stacking_limits assignment). The
per-personality `lim.features` touch lives in raid1_set_limits /
raid10_set_queue_limits and likewise references a struct field absent before
kernel 6.11, so it must be excluded at source level.

This variant matches the COMPOSED meshstor-main tree shape, where the ATOMIC_WRITES
assignment is immediately followed by mddev_stack_rdev_limits() — the member-AND
P2PDMA advertise (commit 0ed31022) having been moved PAST the stack call, where it
is gated separately by 0008. On verbatim upstream `master` an extra
`lim.features |= BLK_FEAT_PCI_P2PDMA` sits between ATOMIC_WRITES and the stack call,
so that shape is handled by 0010 instead. Selection is by the `.when` guard:
0009 applies only when the meshstor helper raid1_can_advertise_p2pdma() is present.

The hunks anchor on a leading line common to both raid personalities' variants and
on the trailing mddev_stack_rdev_limits() call, so they apply at --fuzz=0.

--- a/raid10.c
+++ b/raid10.c
@@ -4391,3 +4391,5 @@
 	lim.io_opt = lim.io_min * raid10_nr_stripes(conf);
+#ifdef HAVE_QUEUE_LIMITS_FEATURES
 	lim.features |= BLK_FEAT_ATOMIC_WRITES;
+#endif
 	err = mddev_stack_rdev_limits(mddev, &lim, MDDEV_STACK_INTEGRITY);
--- a/raid1.c
+++ b/raid1.c
@@ -3339,3 +3339,5 @@
 	lim.logical_block_size = mddev->logical_block_size;
+#ifdef HAVE_QUEUE_LIMITS_FEATURES
 	lim.features |= BLK_FEAT_ATOMIC_WRITES;
+#endif
 	err = mddev_stack_rdev_limits(mddev, &lim, MDDEV_STACK_INTEGRITY);
